ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Alright, you did an unpaid summer internship and need a film credit, why not take this? You give a short presentation to a few peers about your work and write a medium-length paper examining one aspect of the job. Considering how youve already worked so hard, this is a harmless way to receive credit for it, so go for it.
Four lunch meetings throughout the semester, during which each person gives a presentation on their internship from the summer, and at the end hands in a 10 page paper.
If you pick a good subject and have a good professor this is an amazing way to spend a semester.
